cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and specifically focuses on coherence features in paragraphs. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the identification of computer-generated text. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the method used for extracting coherence features involves matching similar words in sentences, which is a common technique in machine learning. It could also be classified under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as the identification of computer-translated paragraphs involves retrieving relevant information from the text. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as the method used for identifying computer-translated paragraphs may involve the use of neural networks or evolutionary algorithms.
